&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot; style=&

&lt;p&gt;Own the words that move the market — hooks, case studies, scripts, and positioning for a product growing 145% YoY.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;On-site | Vancouver Office – 675 W Hastings St.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Problem We&#39;re Solving&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dental labs and clinics across 28 countries run on fragmented workflows — disconnected communication, manual case management, and software that hasn&#39;t been rethought in a generation. EviSmart is replacing that with an intelligent, unified platform: AI-powered crown design, structured case communication, and a dashboard that brings it all together. The product is live, the customers are real, and growth is compounding. What doesn&#39;t exist yet is the narrative layer — the hooks that stop the scroll, the case studies that close deals, and the positioning that makes the entire category reconsider what &quot;good&quot; looks like.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-parastyle=&quot;heading 3&quot;&gt;Why EviSmart&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;300 people. Two hubs: Vancouver HQ and Manila operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;145% year-over-year SaaS growth — the market is responding.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;28 countries. One platform. The dental industry&#39;s Autopilot.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 2;&quot;&gt;An in-house AI model research and development team building proprietary intelligence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why This Role, Right Now&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EviSmart&#39;s product suite is expanding across multiple surfaces simultaneously — an AI-powered design module, a structured communication platform, and a unified operations dashboard launching this year as Command Center. The product is working. What&#39;s missing is the story: customer proof that salespeople can actually use, founder-led content that compounds in the market, and positioning that separates EviSmart from a crowded category. The person who joins now builds the craft layer the entire go-to-market motion runs on.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Note from the Team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&quot;We&#39;re looking for someone whose writing interrupts the pattern — open loops, curiosity, proof over polish. The product is good enough that we don&#39;t need to oversell it. We need someone who can tell the truth about what it does, fast enough that the market hears it before our competitors figure out what hit them.&quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;— Paolo Kalaw, CEO, EviSmart&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-parastyle=&quot;heading 3&quot;&gt;What &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-parastyle=&quot;heading 3&quot;&gt;You’ll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-parastyle=&quot;heading 3&quot;&gt; Own&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134245418&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;13

&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for cleaning, organizing, and maintaining customer and operational data so it can be reliably used for analytics, reporting, and basic modeling. The Data Engineer focuses on making messy data usable, consistent, and trustworthy for the rest of the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on execution role, not a senior or architecture role. Success is measured by how clean, reliable, and easy-to-use the data becomes for analysts, product, and business teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Success Looks Like&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Customer and operational datasets are clean, consistent, and easy to analyze&lt;br&gt;• Data pipelines run reliably with minimal errors&lt;br&gt;• Analysts and stakeholders spend less time fixing data and more time using it&lt;br&gt;• Basic data quality checks are in place and working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Cleanup &amp;amp; Maintenance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Clean, normalize, and join customer, sales, and operational data from multiple sources&lt;br&gt;• Fix broken or unreliable data pipelines and tables&lt;br&gt;• Maintain consistent definitions for core customer and revenue metrics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Pipelines &amp;amp; Modeling&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Build and maintain simple, reliable data pipelines&lt;br&gt;• Create analytics-ready tables to support reporting, dashboards, and analysis&lt;br&gt;• Work with upstream teams to understand source data issues and limitations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Quality &amp;amp; Reliability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Add basic data quality checks to catch missing, incorrect, or inconsistent data&lt;br&gt;• Monitor pipelines and resolve issues when data breaks&lt;br&gt;• Document datasets so others understand how to use them correctly&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Support analysts and data scientists by providing clean, well-structured data&lt;br&gt;• Collaborate with product, sales, and operations teams to understand data needs&lt;br&gt;• Help answer ad-hoc data questions when needed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Reliability and freshness of customer analytics datasets&lt;br&gt;• Reduction in data errors and rework required by analysts&lt;br&gt;• Time to resolve data pipeline issues&lt;br&gt;• Usability and clarity of analytics tables and documentation&lt;br&gt;• Stakeholder satisfaction with data quality and availability&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 2–4 years of experience in data engineering, analytics engineering, or a similar role&lt;br&gt;• Experience working with real-world, imperfect data&lt;br&gt;• Strong SQL skills and working knowledge of Python&lt;br&gt;• Experience building and maintaining data pipelines&lt;br&gt;• Familiarity with cloud data warehouses and ETL/ELT tools&lt;br&gt;• Detail-oriented and patient with messy data&lt;br&gt;• Practical and execution-focused&lt;br&gt;• Comfortable working independently on well-scoped tasks&lt;br&gt;• Able to explain data issues clearly to non-technical teammates&lt;br&gt;• Willing to ask questions and collaborate to resolve data problems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Meaningful impact by improving the foundation of customer analytics&lt;br&gt;• Clear, focused role with realistic expectations&lt;br&gt;• Opportunity to grow technical depth in data engineering and analytics&lt;br&gt;• Collaborative team that values clean, us

